 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Interview Analyst - Spanish Study (Remote, USA) Venga Global North Carolina Remote Job details Salary $15 an hour Job Type Part-time Temporary Full Job Description Description
 
HireVue is hiring Interview Analysts to work for 12 weeks to help improve the interview process for people around the world by making it more fair and giving everyone a shot at getting their perfect job. If you are interested in people, are willing to learn, have great attention to detail, and want to see what itâ€™s like to work for one of the best up-and-coming tech companies, this job is for you.
 
Responsibilities
 
Our Data Science team is working on creating Artificial Intelligence algorithms for their video interview software around a number of personality traits to help predict job success from a video job interview. It sounds complicated, but your part in this is not difficult.
 
You will be trained by our science teams on specific human traits and how to identify them. You will then watch videos in Spanish and identify which traits the person in the video is exhibiting. This will help our team gather enough data to teach computers to identify the same traits. Additional special projects may be assigned if time allows.
 
While this position will be remote, you will be closely collaborating with other Interview analysts, a project manager, and trainers via ongoing video conferencing.
 
Requirements
 
Must be available to work up to 20 hours a week from July 6th - September 30th
 
Stable internet connection
 
A working environment free from distractions
 
Working schedule is 8am-2pm MT Monday-Thursday
 
Pay is $15 / hour
 
Must be able to complete a criminal background check
 
Must be fluent in English and a native speaker and writer in Spanish
 
Must be proficient working on the computer
 
Must be able to focus and work independently for 4-6 hours at a time
 
Must be able to work remotely
 
Position is temporary and will end after 12 weeks
 
Must live and work in the US
 
Must be legally authorized to work in the United States
